The Ebonyi State police command has confirmed the kidnap of two Chinese working in the state by suspected gunmen. The state police commissioner, CP Awosola Awotinde, who announced the incident did not give details. He, however, expressed optimism that the expatriates would be rescued, adding that efforts were being made to trail the kidnappers. LEADERSHIP gathered that they were abducted at Ishiagu, Ivo local government area of the state, where they worked for a mining company. Meanwhile, the Styate Neighbourhood Watch has been mandated to block all entry and exit points of the state and to also be on the lookout for the kidnappers.